{
  "stem": "16930.3",
  "chunk_idx": 15,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 14.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So when the Russians came out to chase these guys, they swooped down on them and knocked off four Russian MiGs with the-- with the inferior planes.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And Ezer Weizmann got one-- scored one of them.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "People think he got to be president of a state because his uncle was president.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He earned it the hard way.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He was an officer and a good officer.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Then he became commander after the other ones, the-- there was a fellow who was from South Africa who was a commander of that-- that particular [NON-ENGLISH] 101-- flight 101-- Squadron 101.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I can't think of the name of the place.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I can't think-- it was in [INAUDIBLE] there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There was an airport in [INAUDIBLE], another one near [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And all the British had left these airports.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The British had built all these airports and army places for their army all over the place, you know?",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So this is what the Israeli-- the-- this is where the-- basically Haganah moved in.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The Haganah moved into the airports where the British left behind.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And army units moved in where the British had built barracks and other things.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And so he got one.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then he subsequently became commander of this squadron subsequently.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then he worked his way up and became chief of the Air Force.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I think he had a big hand, if not the primary hand, when they had this-- when they destroyed the-- the-- the Egyptian Air Force and other air forces, when they did this-- when they-- by surprise, caught him by surprise.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they were flying there and destroyed most of the bridge of the Egyptian Air Force and other air forces on the ground.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was-- I was there for about-- in the air force.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
